div.p:
It is now, and euer was, since that first Easter, a continu'd Feast of ioy, solemniz'd with celestiall Iubiles by the Angels in Heauen, because he brought himselfe vp out of the Graue;
                  Cyp.

               Sed in hoc multiplicata sunt gaudia, saith a Father: This extends the degrees of their accidentall ioy to the height, that we, for whom he became so humble on earth, shall by him be made so high in heauen: That these bodies shall againe be made the glorified Tabernacles to their soules, from which that Diuine part shall neuer againe be frighted with diseases, neuer loaded with discontents, neuer rackt by pashions, neuer tortur'd by affections, neuer vext by griefes, nor expell'd by rebellious frailty; but euery Christian shall bee in a heauen of peace, and the peace of heauen in euery Christian, that is brought vp out of his Graue.
